<component id="ID_txt01">
<text><![CDATA[<ul><li>TCP is a connection-oriented protocol. TCP is used if data packets require guaranteed delivery and must be acknowledged.</li><br/><li>UDP is a connectionless protocol. UDP is used if data packets do not require guaranteed delivery.</li><br/><li>The TCP and UDP protocols use port numbers to map data packets to a specific application, or process that is running on a server.</li><br/><li>TCP and UDP ports enable network servers to quickly and reliably respond to many simultaneous requests for data that are initiated by and destined to separate applications.</li></ul>]]></text>
</component>
