<component id="ID_txt03">
<text><![CDATA[<ul><li>Dynamic Updates enable DNS client computers to register and dynamically update their resource records with a DNS server whenever changes occur.</li><br/><li>DNS zones can be either Forward lookup, or Reverse lookup zones. They can also be either a primary or secondary zones.</li><br/><li>Many ISPs offer caching-only DNS servers.</li><br/><li>An organization may run its own DNS server that can either point to the caching-only server or directly to the root server for name resolution.</li></ul>]]></text>
</component>

